<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">275. Drake, Nicolas. Fashion Illustration Today. London: Thames andHudson, 1987. 175 pp. Color illus. ISBN 0-500-27486-X. </p><p class="annot">This publication brings together the exciting work of 22 leadingillustrators from four great international fashion capitals: New York, Paris, Milan, and London. Comments on color appear in the short introductory text and in the captions on the artist’s purpose that accompany each illustration. The author’s main point is that expressive fashion illustration is triumphing again over photography and color is a vital component of fashion illustration. </p></div>
